Package: TWDeConv
Title: Spatio-Temporal Deconvolution of Moving-Average Estimates
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R:
    person("Yung", "Chun", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "yungchun@wustl.edu",
           comment = c(ORCID = ""))
Description: Provides tools to deconvolve multi-year moving-average spatial
    estimates (e.g., ACS 5-year data) into latent annual signals using a
    Kronecker-structured spatio-temporal generalised lasso solved via the
    Alternating Direction Method of Multipliers (ADMM). Includes a synthetic
    data generator for simulation studies, penalty matrix builders (temporal
    difference, spatial graph Laplacian, precision weights), an efficient ADMM
    solver with one-time Cholesky factorisation for lambda grid searches, a
    simulation suite with RMSE/CCC evaluation, and a complete ACS 5-year data
    ingestion pipeline with Variance Replicate Estimate (VRE) support.
